    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-c758045b
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/accountability-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/accountability-goals/goal-a3-fit-for-purpose/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: use outside intended purpose
  conditions: []
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The provider shall publish documentation to customers that describes the system's
    intended uses.
  evidence: []
  severity: medium
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: “Describes the system's intended uses” is vague—no specific fields/format
      to enable objective automated pass/fail.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-f10146db
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/accountability-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/accountability-goals/goal-a3-fit-for-purpose/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - provider
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: use outside intended purpose
  conditions:
  - system is a platform service made available to external customers or partners
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - When the system is a platform service made available to external customers or
    partners, the provider shall include the intended uses and evidence that the system
    is fit for purpose for each intended use in the required Transparency Note.
  evidence:
  - Transparency Note
  severity: medium
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Verify the Transparency Note document contains an intended-uses list and
      an evidence entry for each use.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-fbf05b5c
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/accountability-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/accountability-goals/goal-a3-fit-for-purpose/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: continued use for an unsupported intended use
  conditions:
  - If an intended use is not supported by evidence, or if evidence comes to light
    that refutes that the system is fit for purpose for the intended use at any point
    in the system's use
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - 'org shall perform at least one of the following: remove the intended use from
    customer-facing materials and notify current customers of the issue; take action
    to close the identified gap; or discontinue the system.'
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Obligation lists concrete actions (remove doc use, notify customers, fix
      gap, or discontinue) verifiable via docs, logs, or service config.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - log_check
    - config_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-f9c33126
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/accountability-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/accountability-goals/goal-a3-fit-for-purpose/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: outdated or misleading documentation about intended use
  conditions:
  - If an intended use is not supported by evidence, or if evidence comes to light
    that refutes that the system is fit for purpose for the intended use at any point
    in the system's use
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall revise documentation related to the intended use.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: '''revise'' and ''documentation related to the intended use'' are vague;
      no objective oracle to decide which docs changed or what counts as revised.'
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-39855825
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/accountability-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/accountability-goals/goal-a3-fit-for-purpose/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: omission from Transparency Note for platform services
  conditions:
  - If an intended use is not supported by evidence, or if evidence comes to light
    that refutes that the system is fit for purpose for the intended use at any point
    in the system's use
  - When the system is a platform service made available to external customers or
    partners
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - org shall include this information in the required Transparency Note.
  evidence: []
  severity: medium
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Unspecified 'this information' — cannot objectively verify inclusion in
      Transparency Note via IO inspection.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
