- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-7819b65f
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/reliability-safety-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/reliability-safety-goals/goal-rs3-ongoing-monitoring-feedback-and-evaluation/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: continued use despite loss of fitness for intended use
  conditions:
  - evidence refutes the system is fit for purpose for an intended use at any point
    in the system's use
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - When evidence refutes that the system is fit for an intended use, the org shall
    remove that intended use from customer-facing materials and make current customers
    aware of the issue.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: true
  testability:
    reason: Removal from customer-facing materials and customer notifications can
      be verified via documentation/repo inspection and notification logs.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - log_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0004-8cc7cc8a
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/reliability-safety-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/reliability-safety-goals/goal-rs3-ongoing-monitoring-feedback-and-evaluation/sent_0004
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: misleading or out-of-date documentation for intended use
  conditions:
  - evidence refutes the system is fit for purpose for an intended use at any point
    in the system's use
  - When the system is a platform service made available to external customers or
    partners
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - When evidence refutes the system is fit for an intended use, the org shall revise
    documentation related to that intended use.
  evidence: []
  severity: high
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: Trigger ('evidence refutes') and required extent/timing of 'revise' are
      not objectively defined for a pass/fail check.
    evidence_signals:
    - repo_check
    - log_check
    - io_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0005-1625a071
  source:
    doc: spans_passthrough_candidates
    citation: index/reliability-safety-goals
    span_id: Microsoft/index/reliability-safety-goals/goal-rs3-ongoing-monitoring-feedback-and-evaluation/sent_0005
  scope:
    actor:
    - org
    data_domain: []
    context: []
  hazard: outdated documentation
  conditions:
  - new uses are added
  - functionality changes
  - new information about reliable and safe performance becomes known as defined by
    requirement RS3.3
  - new information about system accuracy and performance becomes available
  exceptions: []
  requirements:
  - The org shall review and update the documentation required by Goal T2 when any
    of the specified events occur.
  evidence:
  - documentation required by Goal T2
  severity: medium
  is_testable: false
  testability:
    reason: References undefined 'specified events' and Goal T2 and gives no objective
      update criteria or timeframe, so pass/fail is not verifiable.
    evidence_signals:
    - io_check
    - log_check
    - repo_check
- rule_id: spans-passthrough-candidates/sent_0006-a9514df3
